  "prompt": "Do boys get friendzoned?",
  "response": "Yes, absolutely. The concept of being \"friendzoned\" isn't exclusive to any gender. Anyone can experience unrequited romantic feelings for a friend, regardless of their gender identity or sexual orientation.\n\nThe idea behind the \"friendzone\" is that someone desires a romantic relationship with a friend who only wants a platonic relationship. This can happen to anyone.\n\nIt's important to remember that:\n\n*   **Friendship is valuable:** Just because someone doesn't want to date you doesn't mean they don't value you as a person.\n*   **People have the right to choose:** No one is obligated to return romantic feelings, regardless of gender.\n*   **The \"friendzone\" can be a harmful concept:** It can imply that friendship is a consolation prize or that someone is entitled to a romantic relationship simply by being a good friend.\n\nSo, yes, boys get friendzoned just as much as girls do, and it's a common experience for people of all genders.",
